FIFA has charged World Cup hosts Russia with fan racism less than two months before the tournament begins. Monkey chants were aimed at black French players, including Paul Pogba, during France's 3-1 friendly win over Russia in Saint Petersburg last month. After collecting evidence of the abuse, FIFA said 'disciplinary proceedings have been opened against the Russian Football Union for this incident'. Russia was previously charged with racist behavior by its fans at the last two European Championships. On both occasions, the Russian Football Union paid a fine.It's the third racism case this season at Saint Petersburg Stadium, which will host one of the World Cup semi-finals.Zenit Saint Petersburg have twice faced UEFA charges for racism by their fans in Europa League games. -REUTERS